A lack of awareness of some of the rarer causes of recurrent abdominal pain may impede diagnosis and delay effective management. This article identifies some of the key rare but diagnosable causes that are frequently missed by gastroenterologists, and provides expert recommendations to support recognition, diagnosis, and management with the ultimate aim of improving patient outcomes.
